{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ApW39Uqp2u9x17k6SZvGFn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Fix the C code based on the validation failures below.\n     2→Only modify files that need fixing. Do not rewrite the entire project.\n     3→\n     4→Focus on:\n     5→1. Compiler errors and warnings first (must compile with -Wall -Wextra -Werror -pedantic)\n     6→2. Test failures second (read the assertion output carefully)\n     7→3. Memory errors from valgrind (leaks, use-after-free, invalid reads/writes)\n     8→4. Static analysis warnings from cppcheck\n     9→\n    10→Read the error output carefully. Fix the root cause, not symptoms.\n    11→When fixing valgrind errors, trace the allocation back to its source\n    12→and ensure every code path frees it.\n    13→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01EAKuUouRmJ3a4iBQWLZ1wd","session_id":"87510e8f-028e-4687-9903-d33073502bb8","uuid":"c11cecdb-af11-401c-962f-91b370377f78"}
